    "html": "<section class=\"problem\" id=\"4-55\"><h2>4-55</h2><div class=\"tagline\"><span class=\"pill\">Lesson</span> Sorted to Unit 3, Section 1: Graphing and Elimination</div><div class=\"audit\">Audit note: Solves a system in standard form by substitution as setup for elimination.</div>\n<p>Jeanette is trying to find the intersection point of these two equations:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">$$\\begin{aligned}3y+2x&amp;=-2\\\\-3y+5x&amp;=16\\end{aligned}$$</p>\n<p>She has decided to use substitution to find the point of intersection. Her plan is to solve the first equation for $y$, and then to substitute the result into the second equation. Use Jeanette’s idea to solve the system.</p>\n<div class=\"workspace workspace-xl\"></div>\n</section>",
